title: Imtiaz Ahmed of PPPP wins PS-7 seat
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians (PPPP)’ candidate Imtiaz Ahmed Sheikh has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-7 Shikarpur-I constituency by securing 60,354 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Agha Taimur Khan of Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam Pakistan (JUI-P) who bagged 44,480 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 44.82 per cent in the constituency.
